sequenceDiagram
    participant C as Customer
    participant S as Sales Team
    participant F as Finance
    participant FD as Finance Director
    participant IT as IT Ops

    C->>S: Submit onboarding request
    S->>F: Credit check request
    %% ⚡ CHANGED SECTION
    F->>F: Risk Assessment (Score >750, Verified Company, Clean Payment History)
    alt Low-Risk: Score >750 AND Verified AND No Payment Issues
        F-->>S: Auto-Approved (Expedited Path)
        S->>IT: Provision accounts (immediate)
        IT-->>C: Welcome email + credentials (within 24h)
    else High-Risk: Fails any risk criteria
        F->>FD: Escalate for Finance Director approval
        FD-->>F: Approval decision (24h SLA)
        F-->>S: Approval relayed
        S->>IT: Provision accounts
        IT-->>C: Welcome email + credentials
    end
    %% END CHANGED SECTION
    C->>IT: First login confirmation
    IT->>S: Onboarding complete
    S->>C: Kickoff meeting scheduled

%% EXPLANATION:
%% Added a Finance Director participant and replaced the single approval flow with an alt/else block after the credit check. Low-risk customers (score >750, verified company status, clean payment history) are auto-approved by Finance and proceed directly to account provisioning on an expedited path. High-risk customers who fail any of the three criteria are escalated to the Finance Director for manual approval before provisioning, preserving the existing control workflow.